# Android Traffic Interception with Burp Suite

## Objective
Successfully intercept HTTP/HTTPS traffic from an Android device using Burp Suite Community Edition.

## Lab Environment

Host OS = Windows 11
Attacker = VM Kali Linux
Target = Android-x86
Tool = Burp Suite Community
Network = NAT Network

## Prerequisites

- Burp Suite installed
- Android connected to the same network
- Burp CA Certificate
- Proxy listener configured

# Procedure

## Step 1 - Configure Burp Proxy Listener

Open
Proxy → Proxy Settings → Add.

Configure
Interface: 192.168.1.83
Port: 8080

Screenshot
screenshots/01-proxy-listener.png

## Step 2 - Download Burp CA Certificate

Open Android browser.

Visit
http://192.168.1.83:8080

Download
CA Certificate

Screenshot
screenshots/02-download-ca.png

## Step 3 - Install Certificate

Navigate to
Settings → Security & Privacy → More Security & Privacy → Encryption & Credentials → Install a Certificate → CA Certificate → Install Anyway → Select cacert.der

Screenshot
screenshots/03-install-ca.png

## Step 4 - Verify Installation

Navigate to

Settings → Trusted Credentials → User

Verify the Burp certificate is listed.

Screenshot
screenshots/04-trusted-cert.png

## Step 5 - Configure Android Proxy

Navigate to
Settings → Network & Internet → Wi-Fi → Edit Network → Advanced Options → Proxy → Manual

Configure
Host: 192.168.1.83
Port: 8080
Save.

Screenshot
screenshots/05-proxy-config.png

## Step 6 - Intercept Traffic

In Burp

Proxy → Intercept → Intercept is ON

Open any website on Android.

The request appears in Burp.

Click Forward

Turn Intercept OFF.

Open Proxy → HTTP History

Verify captured traffic.

Screenshot
screenshots/06-http-history.png

# Result
Successfully intercepted Android HTTP/HTTPS traffic using Burp Suite.

# Challenges
HTTPS traffic initially failed because the Burp CA certificate was not installed.

Installing the CA certificate resolved the issue.

# Lessons Learned

- Proxy configuration
- CA certificates
- HTTPS interception
- Burp HTTP History
- Android network settings

